arguments.prompt:
You are implementing a Blazor Web App for a logistics company that tracks shipments. The project is already scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-a28fb30266fe44799e8a08aac8e32bae/ShipmentTracker/` with:
- Interactive Auto, Global mode (`-int Auto -ai -au Individual`)
- Two projects: `ShipmentTracker` (server) and `ShipmentTracker.Client` (WebAssembly)
- ASP.NET Core Identity already configured with SQLite

## Requirements:
1. Dispatchers view a list of shipments with status and destination
2. Customers check their shipment status and estimated delivery
3. Every page has interactive controls
4. Staff and customers authenticate with individual accounts

## Architecture (Auto mode rules):
- All interactive components MUST go in `.Client` project under `Pages/`
- Data access from interactive components must go through HTTP APIs (no direct DbContext)
- Define service interfaces in `.Client`, implement with HttpClient there, and with EF Core on server
- Register matching services in both Program.cs files
- Expose server data through minimal API endpoints

## What to implement:

### 1. Data Model (server project)
Create `ShipmentTracker/Data/Shipment.cs`:
```csharp
public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string? CustomerId { get; set; } // links to ApplicationUser.Id
    public string? Description { get; set; }
}

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Cancelled
}
```

### 2. Add Shipment to DbContext
In `ShipmentTracker/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs`, add:
```csharp
public DbSet<Shipment> Shipments => Set<Shipment>();
```

### 3. Shared DTOs/Interfaces in Client project
Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentDto.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public class ShipmentDto
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Status { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string? CustomerId { get; set; }
    public string? Description { get; set; }
}

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetAllShipmentsAsync();
    Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetMyShipmentsAsync();
    Task<ShipmentDto> CreateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto shipment);
    Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, string status);
}
```

### 4. Client-side implementation (HttpClient-based)
Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentHttpService.cs`:
```csharp
using System.Net.Http.Json;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public class ShipmentHttpService(HttpClient http) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
        => await http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<ShipmentDto>>("api/shipments") ?? [];

    public async Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
        => await http.GetFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto?>($"api/shipments/track/{trackingNumber}");

    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetMyShipmentsAsync()
        => await http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<ShipmentDto>>("api/shipments/my") ?? [];

    public async Task<ShipmentDto> CreateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto shipment)
    {
        var response = await http.PostAsJsonAsync("api/shipments", shipment);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto>() ?? shipment;
    }

    public async Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, string status)
    {
        var response = await http.PutAsJsonAsync($"api/shipments/{id}/status", new { Status = status });
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
    }
}
```

### 5. Server-side implementation (EF Core-based)
Create `ShipmentTracker/Services/ShipmentServerService.cs`:
```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization;
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Data;
using System.Security.Claims;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Services;

public class ShipmentServerService(ApplicationDbContext db, AuthenticationStateProvider authStateProvider) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await db.Shipments
            .OrderByDescending(s => s.CreatedAt)
            .Select(s => MapToDto(s))
            .ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        var shipment = await db.Shipments.FirstOrDefaultAsync(s => s.TrackingNumber == trackingNumber);
        return shipment is null ? null : MapToDto(shipment);
    }

    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetMyShipmentsAsync()
    {
        var authState = await authStateProvider.GetAuthenticationStateAsync();
        var userId = authState.User.FindFirstValue(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier);
        return await db.Shipments
            .Where(s => s.CustomerId == userId)
            .OrderByDescending(s => s.CreatedAt)
            .Select(s => MapToDto(s))
            .ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<ShipmentDto> CreateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto dto)
    {
        var shipment = new Shipment
        {
            TrackingNumber = dto.TrackingNumber,
            Origin = dto.Origin,
            Destination = dto.Destination,
            Status = Enum.Parse<ShipmentStatus>(dto.Status),
            CreatedAt = DateTime.UtcNow,
            EstimatedDelivery = dto.EstimatedDelivery,
            CustomerId = dto.CustomerId,
            Description = dto.Description
        };
        db.Shipments.Add(shipment);
        await db.SaveChangesAsync();
        return MapToDto(shipment);
    }

    public async Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, string status)
    {
        var shipment = await db.Shipments.FindAsync(id);
        if (shipment is not null)
        {
            shipment.Status = Enum.Parse<ShipmentStatus>(status);
            await db.SaveChangesAsync();
        }
    }

    private static ShipmentDto MapToDto(Shipment s) => new()
    {
        Id = s.Id,
        TrackingNumber = s.TrackingNumber,
        Origin = s.Origin,
        Destination = s.Destination,
        Status = s.Status.ToString(),
        CreatedAt = s.CreatedAt,
        EstimatedDelivery = s.EstimatedDelivery,
        CustomerId = s.CustomerId,
        Description = s.Description
    };
}
```

### 6. API Endpoints
Create `ShipmentTracker/Endpoints/ShipmentEndpoints.cs`:
```csharp
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Data;
using System.Security.Claims;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Endpoints;

public static class ShipmentEndpoints
{
    public static void MapShipmentEndpoints(this WebApplication app)
    {
        var group = app.MapGroup("api/shipments").RequireAuthorization();

        group.MapGet("/", async (ApplicationDbContext db) =>
        {
            var shipments = await db.Shipments
                .OrderByDescending(s => s.CreatedAt)
                .ToListAsync();
            return shipments.Select(MapToDto);
        });

        group.MapGet("/track/{trackingNumber}", async (string trackingNumber, ApplicationDbContext db) =>
        {
            var shipment = await db.Shipments.FirstOrDefaultAsync(s => s.TrackingNumber == trackingNumber);
            return shipment is null ? Results.NotFound() : Results.Ok(MapToDto(shipment));
        });

        group.MapGet("/my", async (ClaimsPrincipal user, ApplicationDbContext db) =>
        {
            var userId = user.FindFirstValue(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier);
            var shipments = await db.Shipments
                .Where(s => s.CustomerId == userId)
                .OrderByDescending(s => s.CreatedAt)
                .ToListAsync();
            return shipments.Select(MapToDto);
        });

        group.MapPost("/", async (ShipmentDto dto, ClaimsPrincipal user, ApplicationDbContext db) =>
        {
            var shipment = new Shipment
            {
                TrackingNumber = string.IsNullOrEmpty(dto.TrackingNumber) 
                    ? GenerateTrackingNumber() 
                    : dto.TrackingNumber,
                Origin = dto.Origin,
                Destination = dto.Destination,
                Status = Enum.TryParse<ShipmentStatus>(dto.Status, out var s) ? s : ShipmentStatus.Pending,
                CreatedAt = DateTime.UtcNow,
                EstimatedDelivery = dto.EstimatedDelivery,
                CustomerId = dto.CustomerId ?? user.FindFirstValue(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier),
                Description = dto.Description
            };
            db.Shipments.Add(shipment);
            await db.SaveChangesAsync();
            return Results.Created($"api/shipments/{shipment.Id}", MapToDto(shipment));
        });

        group.MapPut("/{id}/status", async (int id, StatusUpdateRequest request, ApplicationDbContext db) =>
        {
            var shipment = await db.Shipments.FindAsync(id);
            if (shipment is null) return Results.NotFound();
            if (Enum.TryParse<ShipmentStatus>(request.Status, out var status))
            {
                shipment.Status = status;
                await db.SaveChangesAsync();
                return Results.Ok();
            }
            return Results.BadRequest("Invalid status");
        });
    }

    private static string GenerateTrackingNumber()
        => $"SHP-{DateTime.UtcNow:yyyyMMdd}-{Random.Shared.Next(10000, 99999)}";

    private static ShipmentDto MapToDto(Shipment s) => new()
    {
        Id = s.Id,
        TrackingNumber = s.TrackingNumber,
        Origin = s.Origin,
        Destination = s.Destination,
        Status = s.Status.ToString(),
        CreatedAt = s.CreatedAt,
        EstimatedDelivery = s.EstimatedDelivery,
        CustomerId = s.CustomerId,
        Description = s.Description
    };
}

public record StatusUpdateRequest(string Status);
```

### 7. Register services and endpoints in server Program.cs
Add before `var app = builder.Build();`:
```csharp
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentServerService>();
```
Add the using at top:
```csharp
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Services;
```
Add before `app.Run();`:
```csharp
app.MapShipmentEndpoints();
```

### 8. Register services in client Program.cs
Update to:
```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.Hosting;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

var builder = WebAssemblyHostBuilder.CreateDefault(args);

builder.Services.AddAuthorizationCore();
builder.Services.AddCascadingAuthenticationState();
builder.Services.AddAuthenticationStateDeserialization();

builder.Services.AddScoped(sp => new HttpClient { BaseAddress = new Uri(builder.HostEnvironment.BaseAddress) });
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentHttpService>();

await builder.Build().RunAsync();
```

### 9. Pages in Client project

**Remove the default template pages** - delete `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/Counter.razor` and `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/Weather.razor` if they exist. Also delete `ShipmentTracker/Components/Pages/Home.razor`, `Counter.razor`, `Weather.razor` if present.

**Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/Home.razor`:**
```razor
@page "/"
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization
@using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services
@inject IShipmentService ShipmentService
@attribute [Authorize]

<PageTitle>ShipmentTracker - Dashboard</PageTitle>

<h1>Shipment Dashboard</h1>

<div class="row mb-4">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Track a Shipment</h5>
                <div class="input-group">
                    <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter tracking number..."
                           @bind="trackingNumber" @bind:event="oninput" @onkeydown="HandleKeyDown" />
                    <button class="btn btn-primary" @onclick="TrackShipment" disabled="@string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(trackingNumber)">
                        Track
                    </button>
                </div>
                @if (trackedShipment is not null)
                {
                    <div class="alert alert-info mt-3">
                        <strong>@trackedShipment.TrackingNumber</strong><br />
                        Status: <span class="badge bg-@GetStatusColor(trackedShipment.Status)">@trackedShipment.Status</span><br />
                        Destination: @trackedShipment.Destination<br />
                        @if (trackedShipment.EstimatedDelivery.HasValue)
                        {
                            <span>Estimated Delivery: @trackedShipment.EstimatedDelivery.Value.ToString("MMM dd, yyyy")</span>
                        }
                    </div>
